values: Well... it's not even noon and its hotter than hell...... i'm unpacked.... pretty much settled in.... and it feels like home :-) and I couldn't be happier.

So I got the dress today. I'll be getting it around the beginning of October. It is absolutely stunning. I'd post details except I want it to be a surprise for the most part and I REALLY want to surprise Tim. And it seem like good news just keeps coming. Ashley is doing good! She had another surgery this morning but shes doing good, she is such a fighter. I'm so proud of her. So between moving and the dress and all the other excitement... Well, lets just say it'll be a wonder if I sleep much in the next couple nights.

Bad poetry... The Dream Every time it starts the same, Almost with the same terrain. I stand there on the ground Can't help but look around To see my sisters play On a bright sunny day. I try to run Share their fun, But that's when it starts to come undone. I climb the latter And here their chatter As they cross the bridge. The unheard of, rickety, crickety old bridge. My heart beats faster, My breath grows shorter, I grow weaker, Time grows longer. And when I reach that ledge, Following my sisters on the bridge I start to fall. Fall forever. Fall with speed. Fall to nowhere. Until I scream! And see it's over.

I know this is rough, but it came to me the other night.




I've tried my best 
To find those words 
That could express
What you mean to me

I've turned my world all around,
Shaking it up and down
To see if the words fall out
That say all I want to say
Of what you mean to me

To say I love you
Doesn't really say it
To know I miss you
Only makes it worse
To feel your touch
Makes me burn for more

I search my world harder
Searching for the words
I stumble across a memory
A memory of just us two

I remember the night
The night I knew it was true
As the music played
For just us two

I knew my life had changed
I knew I'd never be the same

You leaned on me
Just before you feel asleep
I whispered in your ear
I breathed in deep

I knew my life had changed
I knew I'd never be the same

I've tried my best
To mold my words
To make them tell you
What you mean to me

Now, I sit here 
Trying to explain
It hurts 
When I can't be there
I cry 
When you're away
I'm sad
When I can't see you
I die 
When you're in pain

I've tried my best
You know I have
You've been there 
Thick and thin

If only I could 
Find those words
That truly express
What you mean to me.

But I have to let the few people who may possibly read this know what has happened.

As of Friday January 6th Tim and I are engaged.

He made me this wonderful 4 course dinner (yummy salad, mouth watering bread sticks, wonderful pizza and to top it all off... pumpkin pie) and when he came out with my slice of pumpkin pie he had the ring on the plate and got down on one knee and asked me to marry him. I cried like you don't understand, and of course I said yes. 

We spent all of yesterday on the road going to tell my parents (well really just seeing them, Tim asked Dad for permission and then Dad told Becky and Mom. So really we just stopped to see them and call debbie and tell my grandparents). Then we were off to see his parents. His dad knew about it but his mom didn't have a clue and freaked out. We went out to a wonderful dinner and then 3 hours all the way back to Dubuque.


No dates have been set yet. 

Tim and I are waiting to hear from UW-Platteville. We would like to see if it's possible for me to transfer and not get held back much (if any) more. I'm hoping I can because Platteville is 15 minutes from Dubuque and well I have a 45 to Whitewater. And as Tim said, the most important thing is school. Our wedding can wait a little while if we need it to, no point in getting married and then not being able to see each other more than weekends.

Chapter VIII

Highest good is like water. Because water excels in benifiting the myriad creatures without contending wiht them and settles where none would like to be, it comes close to the way.
   In a home it is the site that matters;
   In quality of mind it is depth that matters;
   In an ally it is benevolence that matters;
   In speech it is good faith that matters;
   In government it is order that matters;
   In affairs it is ability that matters;
   In action it is timeliness that matters.
It is because it does not contend that it is never at fault. 


Chapter XXXVII

The way never acts yet nothing is left undone.
Should lords and princes be able to hold fast to it,
The myriad creatures will be transformed of their own accord.
After they are trasnformed, should desire raise its head,
I shall press it down with the weight of the nameless uncarved block.
The nameless uncarved block
Is but freedom from desire,
And if I cease to desire and remain still,
The empire will be at peace of its own accord.


Chapter XL

Turning back is how the way moves;
Weakness is the means the way employs.
The myriad creatures in the world are born from Something, and Something from Nothing.

So I survived my sisters wedding, although it feels like a big blur now. 
I mean between flying down there at the ass crack of dawn (which ment only seeing my Timby for a little while) and then finally getting there only to have to wait around for debbies flight 2 hours later (which was late) and then having to sit in the car for another 2 hours to get to the hotel (oye). And that was just the beginning. Then Becky starts asking me to try to get the family going as quickly as I can so we dont have to walk a half a mile for parking. Well of  course we didn't get going when she had hoped, and of course there was the big debate about breakfast which we ended up just munching for. In the car i hear nothing but complaining about how horrible this is and absurd it is that becky is having us do this for her wedding, dressing up and etc, to which i wanted to say "hey, if this was a wedding by our standards of traditional, making people do stuff they may not be comfortable wtih we wouldnt think a second thought because its tradition, shes choosing a diffrent path, we should respect that" but i didnt really feel like picking a fight which debbie would have seen that as me picking a fight. But anyways, it was a fun day. I can't say its something I'd do very often, I'd probably do it more if I didnt have to dress up in period clothes and address people as "my lady" and what not. But the shopping was fun, and I sat and talked to a lady whos sister did glass etching which was way cool and she, herself, did jewerly making and they were just wonderfully tallented and just very wonderful people. I got Tim a glass that had a classic English scrollish thing on it from them and was very tempted to get a few other things. I think that's the only reason why I'd really want to go back, I mean watching the fights and stuff was ok and all but the fun little shops were the best, and to get that I could just go to a craft fare. There was one guy who I got a knife/mini sword and a silk umbrella from who was a POW from WWII and just a very interesting guy to talk to. I was a little upset that Debbie and Mom just took Raven for the day and didn't let me spend much time with her, but I did have a little time holding her durring the wedding. Which btw was very interesting, I can't exactly put it all into words but it was very beautiful (and so was Becky's dress, oh my god i dont remember the last time i saw her so dolled up and soo beautiful) But it was a very nice wedding and Alen gave my parents some gifts of very expensive, very rare books. After that we saw the court thing and then was mostly tired and didnt really want to stick around cause of the rain so Becky temporarly came with Dad, Debbie, Mom, Mary, Joel, Renee and I to get Raven settled into the hotel room with us and I have to admit i was a little cranky to have that many people in a room bairly bigger than my bed room when i was so sweaty and tired.  But anyways, thats not the best part of the night. This is the most interesting part of the night... i suppose "best" is not the word to be using:

So Raven is settled in for a little while and Dad, Debbie, Mom and I are all kinda settling in and resting our feet, being able to spread out for the first time in a while since everyone else left when theres a knock on the door. Alen came over asking for Dad's tools because becky and temporarly put her real wedding ring on her right hand with a ring she's been wearing for a while because her wedding was also a wedding for their personas in the SCA (if that didnt make sence, let me know i'll try to explaine it the best that i can). Ne whos so these two rings are cutting off the circulation to her finger on her right hand and Alen and Dad are trying everythign they can to break this ring and they bairly scratched it. So finally we call 911 to see if they can help and they get all the way out there only to find out they dont have a ring cutter, so we're just about to pile a bunch of people into a car to take Becky to the hospital hoping they would have a ring cutter but just then the fire department calls saying that they found a ring cutter and are on their way. So they get there and after a few minutes of sawing with this cutter the ring is finally off and they cut the other ring off and Beckys hand is returning back to normal. Now heres the kicker, earlier when Becky was showing Alen the ring asking if this was an ok ring for a wedding ring he starts laughing and says "sure, if thats the one you really like, then thats the one u can have" and after a little while becky finally gets him to tell her that the ring was worn by German Women who COULDN'T find a husband, which figures that would be the ring Becky would pick out. So later, when the rings are off and shes comfortable, we all have a little laugh about that and the night continues. 

The next day (sunday) wasnt very eventful, we packed into the car, said our good byes (which i think i'm the only one who really wanted to say good bye to Alen but i'll get into this later) and drop debbie off at the airport and then head on our drive straight back to madison. Finally getting home and not wanting to move once getting here. Now with debbie in the car and with out we had the same conversation twice. Debbie and Mom don't like Alen, Dad and I arnt totally thrilled with him but hey, whatever, he makes becky happy and its her choice, we should support that. Now Debbie and Mom just start complaining about beckys choice saying she coulda done better and blah blah blah and i'm 3 seconds away from saying durring both conversations "dude, it doesnt matter, hes family now, he deserves to be treated like family, if for no other reason because Becky deams him worthy of it" but again, i didnt really feel like picking a fight and mom and debbie would have seen it as me picking a fight so i kept my mouth shut. Which the aquard scilence was covered up soon with mom chiming in saying "but i do approve of Tim, hes a very good guy." so i'm figuring i now have my mom and dads blessing on marring Tim when that comes around to being an appropreate time. 

Now i'm sitting here missing my Timby cause its been a long weekend and i didnt get my fill of Timby time and i'm drinking the worlds weirdest beer, i cant even begin to describe it, tim says it tastes like bananas but i dont taste that, i dont know what i taste. and i'm watching the news on Katrina slowly trying to see if i can find any information about my old Online friend Emile (or better known by his Middle name, Simon) to find out if he's ok or what. Last I heard he was in New Orleans, but who knows.

As of now... nothing.

My parents rolled out of here about 8:00 this morning for florida and Becky's wedding. What do I do when their gone? CLEAN. So far i've cleaned:

-the living room (plus vaccuming)
-the bird cage
-the cat boxes
-the frount hall
-the dinning room
-the kitchen (including the fridge thank you very much)

i've also done laundry and will probably end up doing dishes tonight. 

so i'm dead....

You see, it's like inserting tab A into slot B. Only you do it a lot of times and the result can be more boxes if you're not careful, or worse yet, tab A gets something from slot B and falls off. Or slot B gets something from tab A and then you have to smear goopy cream all over slot B, during which time inserting tab A into slot B is just not going to happen, what kind of slot do you think B is anyways? Meanwhile, tab A is busily being inserted into slot C or D, without even so much as a phone call the day after. And tab M just looks on just wishing it could be tab A, because nice tabs never get any slots. And then there's tab F who actually likes tab R, but isn't sure if tab R folds that way. Slot C eventually finds out about slot D and they all find out about slot B, who in turn finds out about slot C and D and in a vengeful plot, tears tab A from its box in a fit of passion. Slot C ends up meeting tab M, and it turns out tab M fits perfectly into slot C--no jostling or forceful cramming at all. Tab and slot C are joined forever by tab K, who has sworn not to insert itself into anything and a few months later, there are new tabs and slots and everyone, except for A, is happy.

 And that, my son, is how corrugated cardboard boxes are made.
